    "eyebrow": "Social Conditions",
    "num": "04",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">04</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Social Conditions</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Demographics and Immigration in Early Texas</h2><ul><li>Anglo-American settlers were encouraged to immigrate to Texas</li><li>Tejanos (Mexican Texans) formed a significant cultural group</li><li>Tensions arose from cultural differences and language barriers</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texas’s population was a mix of Anglo settlers and Tejanos, whose differing cultures and loyalties created social tensions under Mexican rule. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Examine how immigration policies influenced Texas’s demographic makeup.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss how cultural diversity can both enrich and complicate governance.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking the role of Tejanos as active participants, not just background figures.</p></div></div>",
