    "eyebrow": "Economic and Legal Issues",
    "num": "05",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">05</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Economic and Legal Issues</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Slavery and Mexican Law in Texas</h2><ul><li>Mexico outlawed slavery, but many settlers brought enslaved people</li><li>Conflicting laws created tensions between settlers and Mexican authorities</li><li>Slavery was a key issue contributing to unrest</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Mexican government’s anti-slavery laws conflicted with the economic interests of many Anglo settlers who relied on enslaved labor, heightening tensions. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Analyze how slavery laws affected settler-government relations in Texas.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Consider why slavery was a contentious issue in Texas under Mexican rule.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring slavery’s central role in the conflict’s causes.</p></div></div>",
