    "eyebrow": "Political Tensions",
    "num": "06",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">06</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Political Tensions</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Centralist Policies and Settler Resistance</h2><ul><li>Santa Anna’s centralist government reduced Texas’s autonomy</li><li>Settlers opposed loss of local control and Mexican military presence</li><li>Tensions escalated toward armed conflict</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The shift to centralism under Santa Anna removed local governance powers, provoking resistance from settlers who valued autonomy and feared military repression. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Discuss how centralization policies can provoke rebellion in distant territories.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Explain why settlers might prefer federalism over centralism.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming settlers were simply rebellious without political cause.</p></div></div>",
