    "eyebrow": "Key Battles",
    "num": "08",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">08</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Key Battles</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">The Siege of the Alamo: Defiance and Sacrifice</h2><ul><li>February–March 1836: Mexican forces besieged the Alamo mission</li><li>Famous defenders included Davy Crockett and William B. Travis</li><li>Though a defeat, it became a rallying cry for Texas independence</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Alamo siege was a pivotal event symbolizing Texan courage and sacrifice, galvanizing support for independence despite the loss. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Examine how the Alamo’s legacy influenced Texan morale and recruitment.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss why a military defeat might strengthen a revolutionary cause.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing the Alamo only as a military loss without understanding its symbolic power.</p></div></div>",
