    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">11</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Republic Formation</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Establishing the Republic of Texas</h2><ul><li>Adopted a constitution modeled on U.S. principles</li><li>Sam Houston elected as first president</li><li>Set up government institutions and military</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Following independence, Texas formed a republic with its own constitution and leadership, laying the foundation for self-governance. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s14\">[14]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Compare the Texas Constitution with the U.S. Constitution in structure and rights.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss challenges in creating a new government after revolution.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming immediate stability after independence without transitional challenges.</p></div></div>",
